$ mkdir hadoop_docker
$ cd hadoop_docker
$ git clone https://github.com/m-semnani/bd-infra.git
$ cd bd-infra

COMMAND FOR DOCKER execution to run the hadoop:
  a] docker container ls
  b] docker exec -it <containerID> /bin/bash
  
INSTALLING NIFI ON DOCKER:
a. docker pull apache/nifi:latest
b. docker run --name nifi -p 8443:8443 -e NIFI_WEB_HTTPS_PORT='8443' -d apache/nifi:latest
c. docker logs -f nifi 

# Look for this in the log. It means it has started the nifi server and you can access it.
	INFO [main] org.apache.nifi.web.server.JettyServer https://4cdc79d1487f:8443/nifi
	
  # Scroll up to check these entries in the log. These are default generated username and password for the NIFI UI.
	Generated Username [xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx]
	Generated Password [xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx]
	
d. To change the default username and password: 
	docker run --name nifi -p 8443:8443 -e SINGLE_USER_CREDENTIALS_USERNAME=admin -e SINGLE_USER_CREDENTIALS_PASSWORD=ctsBtRBKHRAx69EqUghvvgEvjnaLjFEB -d apache/nifi:latest
  
e. Try to access the link :https://localhost:8443/nifi . Depending upon the setting of your security, you may get "connection is not private" warning. Ignore it and the grant the access.
f. Enter the username and password when prompted and start working. Cheers..!
